


       
      A former Anglican bishop quoting an Israeli poet;   The Place Where We Are Right   From the place where we are right flowers will never grow in the spring.  The place where we are right is hard and trampled like a yard.  But doubts and loves dig up the world like a mole, a plow.  And a whisper will be heard where the ruined house once stood.   Richard Holloway reciting Yehuda Amichai June 2001.   
     

    
